                    <span>I must have read at least a dozen books on data modeling and database design in the past few years, and this one sits right near the top for ease of understanding and presentation.  The author goes through the material in a logical manner, and writes in a clear way that many other authors on this topic can't even come close to.  I'd recommend this book especially to those new to the field, but there is still useful material for those who have been working/dabbling here for some time.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">THE Book on Data Modeling</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>7</span>
                      /
                      <span>8</span>
